snippet.title: Three Great Appetizers
snippet.description: ... ... There must be many tasty appetizers, and what’s tasty depends, of course, on taste. But I can think of three that taste wonderful to me. ... ... Salsa ... Here is the West the most popular is undoubtedly salsa. Still, I can remember only one restaurant (in Santa Barbara) that served salsa thick enough for my palate. And I certainly can’t recommend any store-bought salsa. ... ... So I make it at home. My favorite recipe is so simple. I just throw chives, cilantro, garlic, stewed tomatoes, serrano peppers, salt, and pepper in my electric blender and pulse for just a second or two. Susan’s recipe for “Simple Texas Salsa” is my absolute favorite. ... ... Since salsa is basically tomatoes, it can’t raise your blood glucose too much, so... ...
